 <Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >
Features
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>The labels display statistics based on the values in the grid view. As users edit items or delete rows in the grid view, the labels automatically maintain the proper values through the grouping engine.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold"  >
Interactive Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0"><ListItem><Paragraph xml:space="preserve"> The program inserts random numbers into a data-table object that has been set as the data source of a grouping engine object. This means that the engine is dynamically monitoring the numbers and maintaining the statistics as each new item is added to the collection.</Paragraph></ListItem></List>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0"><ListItem><Paragraph xml:space="preserve"> <Bold>Generate New Data </Bold> - Clicking on this button with the additional customization of rows in numeric updown will generate random data, and using the displayed data, basic max/min operation of columns can be retrevied.</Paragraph></ListItem></List> 



